title: Bug 110566 - Wrong data set result returned when setting an invalid filter expression row[0]
description: When setting a filter like "row[0] equals to 0", the result set is not returned correctly. Instead, it returns null.
OB: The data set result is not returned correctly when setting an invalid filter expression row[0].
EB: A relevant error message should pop up when setting an invalid filter expression.
SR: Provide a fix for bug 110566 to ensure the correct data set result is returned when setting an invalid filter expression row[0].
